title: CS 161 INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER SCIENCE I
description: Overview of fundamental concepts of computer science. Introduction to problem solving, software engineering, and object-oriented programming. Includes algorithm design and program development. Lec/lab/rec. MTH 112* [C] or Placement Test MPT(33) or Placement Test MPAL(061) and for CS Double Degree students: BA/BS and (MTH 111 or MPT>=24 or MPAL>=061)
